courses.description:
This course will cover the basics of mobile robotics in a hands-on format using the platforms and props develop in MIT's Duckietown project (http://duckietown.mit.edu/). Students will purchase and assemble their own Duckiebots (about $150 each), and then use them throughout the course to test theories and algorithms studied. The topics include: motion control, obstacle avoidance, the “bug” algorithms, simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM), and motion planning. Students interested in taking this course should send
 email to trink@cs.rpi.edu. If there are particular topics
 that you hope will be covered in the class, please include them in the email. Prerequisites: CSCI 2300 and permission of instructor}

